{{doc/start}}
Renders a styled infobox for a pipe element (fluid or gas). Data is pulled automatically from [[Module:Data/Elements]]. The infobox displays the element's name, description, physical state (Gas or Liquid), and pipe color (shown as a color swatch with its hex value).

Pages using this template are auto-generated by <code>foundry_parser generate-pages</code>. Editors can add content below the infobox but should not modify the template call itself.

== Data source ==
Element data comes from [[Module:Data/Elements]], which is auto-generated by running:
<pre>foundry_parser generate-lua</pre>
from the game installation at <code>F:\SteamLibrary\SteamApps\common\FOUNDRY</code>. Do not edit data modules directly.

== Usage ==
<pre>
{{Infobox Element|id=_base_water}}
{{Infobox Element|id=_base_water|image=Water.png}}
</pre>

== Parameters ==
{| class="wikitable"
! Parameter !! Description !! Type !! Status
|-
| <code>id</code> || Element template identifier from the game data (e.g. <code>_base_water</code>). || String || Required
|-
| <code>image</code> || Image filename to display. The module prepends <code>Item_</code> automatically. Element images are typically stored as <code>File:Item_NAME (Element).png</code>. || String || Optional
|}

== Notes ==
* State is derived from the <code>pipe_content_type</code> field: <code>1</code> = Gas, <code>2</code> = Liquid.
* Pipe color is rendered as a small inline color swatch followed by the hex code.
* The infobox automatically adds <code>[[Category:Elements]]</code>.
{{doc/end}}
